  "description": "Tom Paul Berthil Bonde was a Swedish district prosecutor and active in various organizations, including the Slite Municipality, the Gotland Shooting Association, and the Swedish Red Cross. He was born on August 3, 1903, in Kalmar, to goldsmith Claes B. Bonde and Hanna Sofia Jonsson. He married agricultural candidate Alfhild Almgren in 1934 and had one child, Ingrid, in 1937. Bonde completed his realexamen in 1919 and became a district prosecutor in 1927. He served as a lieutenant in the Gotland Infantry Regiment during conscription and went on reserve duty to Germany in 1932, serving in Germany, Holland, Belgium, and France in 1936. He served as an assistant and acting district prosecutor in Kalmar from 1924-1933 before becoming a district prosecutor in Shte in 1933. Bonde had a number of hobbies, including shooting and forestry." 
